                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1674.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-08T08:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 8, 1915—8 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Rebellious Puerto Plata officeholders have agreed to turn over offices to the
                    Dominican Government. President Jiménes has ordered suspension of military
                    movement toward Puerto Plata.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
